{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17646400","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17646400"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T20:29:53+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T20:29:53+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18179"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"18179","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/18179"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.26,0.13,0.03,0.42,0.16]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10893"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"78410"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"10893","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/10893"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18179"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"63772"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4927"},{"type":"tags","id":"4931"},{"type":"tags","id":"4941"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"25332"},{"type":"contributions","id":"25335"},{"type":"contributions","id":"26874"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"78410","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/78410"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EThe muscles of the spine play various roles in movement and stability. Some muscles are involved in extending and laterally flexing the trunk, while others assist in stabilising the ribs during respiration. One of these muscles extends and laterally flexes the trunk and fixes the 12th rib during inspiration.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is this muscle?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["External oblique","Internal oblique","Psoas minor","Quadratus lumborum","Psoas major"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Equadratus lumborum\u003C/strong\u003E muscle is responsible for extending and laterally flexing the trunk. It also plays a crucial role in stabilising the 12th rib during inspiration, which is important for effective breathing.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPsoas major\u003C/strong\u003E - Primarily involved in hip flexion\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EInternal oblique\u003C/strong\u003E - Involved in trunk rotation and lateral flexion, but not rib fixation\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EExternal oblique\u003C/strong\u003E - Also involved in trunk rotation and lateral flexion, but not rib fixation\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPsoas minor\u003C/strong\u003E - Assists in flexing the lumbar spine, but does not fix the rib\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["The quadratus lumborum muscle extends and laterally flexes the trunk.","The quadratus lumborum muscle stabilises the 12th rib during inspiration.","The quadratus lumborum is located in the posterior abdominal wall."],"references":["West, S. G. (2019). Anatomy and physiology of the musculoskeletal system. Rheumatology Secrets E-Book: Rheumatology Secrets E-Book, 17","Henson B, Kadiyala B, Edens MA. Anatomy, Back, Muscles. [Updated 2023 Aug 14]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan-. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK537074/","Hutson, M., \u0026 Ward, A. (Eds.). (2015). Oxford textbook of musculoskeletal medicine. Oxford University Press","Rockwood, C. A., Wirth, M. A., \u0026 Fehringer, E. V. (2016). Rockwood and Matsen\u0027s The Shoulder E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences","DeSai C, Reddy V, Agarwal A. Anatomy, Back, Vertebral Column. [Updated 2023 Aug 8]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan-. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK525969/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"63772"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18179"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"63772","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/63772"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-01-10T17:17:51+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-10T17:18:50+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10893"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"78410"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level I","synonyms":null,"description":"Remember (identifying and retrieving information)","position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"7"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"4927","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/4927"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\udec1","name":"Respiratory","synonyms":[],"descr